Real Sociedad Defeats Barcelona 2-1 in Spain; Real Madrid Loses

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-04-30T20:49:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-30/real-sociedad-defeats-barcelona-2-1-in-spain-real-madrid-loses.html
Barcelona lost 2-1 at Real Sociedad
but maintained its eight-point lead in Spanish soccer’s Primera
Liga as Real  Madrid  was beaten 3-2 by Real Zaragoza.  Diego Ifran and Xabi Prieto scored in the second half as
Sociedad ended Barcelona’s 31-game unbeaten run in the league.
Angel Lafita scored twice in Real Zaragoza’s win at Real Madrid.  Barcelona needs just four points from its final four games
to win its third consecutive league title. It leads Real Madrid
2-0 in their Champions League semifinal ahead of the second leg
in Barcelona in three days.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  